memberdef.name: RPCParseCommandLine

detaileddescription.para: Split shell command line into a list of arguments and optionally execute the command(s). Aims to emulate bash and friends.

listitem.para: Command nesting is possible with parenthesis; for example: validateaddress(getnewaddress())
Arguments are delimited with whitespace or comma
Extra whitespace at the beginning and end and between arguments will be ignored

The backslash \ is used as escape character
Outside quotes, any character can be escaped
Within double quotes, only escape " and backslashes before a \c " or another backslash
Within single quotes, no escaping is possible and no special interpretation takes place

parameterdescription.para: optional node to execute command on
stringified result from the executed command(chain)
set true if you want the command to be executed
